caption: Great food and the staff has been very friendly every time i go in. Always enjoy going!

The meat was juicy and the marinara was flavorful, too. But I would’ve liked more melted cheese.

This is a pretty good spot to get a quick breakfast sandwich before work. They open really early (one of the earliest places in the neigborhood, really,) and they're quite reasonably priced for what you get. Their "famous steak and cheese" comes loaded with significantly more than steak and cheese, and is definitely a messy eat. Their steak, egg, and cheese is a cleaner act, though it's a breakfast exclusive.  These guys are most famous for their hot subs, and going into a restaurant for a cold cut sub is pointless considering there's a Star Market with a bakery and a fully functional deli a block and a half away. You can make your own cold cut sandwich for cheaper, I promise.  Overall, pretty great. They have their own brand of soda too (???) and it's pretty good (?????????) Quick tip - since they have Cape Cod chips, nobody's gonna judge you if you lift the top of your sandwich and sneak a few chips under there. It adds some good crunch and flavor.

I am a frequent visitor at Bennett's, one particular location, Fenway. I have had less than pleasant experiences there in the past, my order is almost always incorrect, but the food IS good so I decided to try it again. I met my wits end today when I placed my order online for pick up. When I sat down to eat my food at work , what I had ordered was not what was sitting in front of me. That's fine, we all make mistakes. Nobody is perfect. But for me to call back and have the actual OWNER of the store tell me that I am wrong and that my sandwich was made correctly because he watched the kid make my sandwich. I said "excuse me?" He told me I was lying. HAHAHAH, I asked him "Are you for real? Am I being punk'd right now? Where's Ashton?" He preceded to tell me what he THOUGHT was on my sandwich, and he couldn't have been more wrong. He told me the only item he forgot was the hot relish. I told him that he left out 4 of the 5 toppings I asked for and he said "No I did not." I told him Id come back and throw it in his face so he could see up close how wrong he got it. He says "I am not trying to argue with you" I said "But you are, you're telling me I am wrong, why do you treat your customers like that?" I just hung up the phone, needless to say I will not be going back.
